    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "How many engines do you have? A task will never be retried on the same engine, so if it's going to fail every time, it will not finish failing unless you have more engines than retries. You can also set a timeout for tasks, which will allow them to fail if they do not succeed within a specified amount of time from submission:\n\n``` python\nview.timeout = 10 # seconds\n```\n"
