    "created_at": "2014-02-14T18:13:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-02-14T18:13:41Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Only the Client knows that the collection of tasks (1 msg_id == 1 task) are associated with each other. The timeout is applied to each task, so they can each timeout separately. Since they are all submitted at the same time, the practical effect (most of the time) is that they will all timeout together.  But the Scheduler evaluating the timeout does not know that they are related to each other.\n"
